name: Angels & Demons

description:
Catwoman is back, and she's on a mission to clean up Gotham City's East End!

Catwoman's pal Holly uses her street smarts to investigate a drug operation, but her snooping lands her in life-threatening danger when she stumbles onto the scene of a murder. Now, with Holly framed for killing a cop, Catwoman must take on seedy criminals and a corrupt police force in a race to uncover the truth and save her friend!

This trade paperback collects Catwoman #5-10 (featuring the story arc "Disguises") and selected stories and character profiles from Catwoman Secret Files and Origins #1.
name: Catwoman: Crooked Little Town

description: Fifth.

The First Shocking Suspense Series from Minotaur!

Brian Cohn is a diagnosed schizophrenic leading a simple, uncomplicated life in Monroeville, Pennsylvania. He’s expecting his first child with his wife. When he goes to visit his estranged Alzheimer’s afflicted father on his deathbed, the dying old man confesses to being a serial killer. Now Brian is faced with discovering a horrifying new side to his father and left wondering if we ever really escape familial legacies.

From acclaimed author Joshua Hale Fialkov (Tumor, Pilot Season: Alibi) and rising artist Rahsan Ekedal (Creepy) a disturbing story of murder and mystery wrapped in questions of sanity.
Spirit
Spirit

Matt's sister Candy is back with the power of a videogame character - and the trouble has just begun! On the run from Korben and a group of mysterious government agents, Matt and Candy are ambushed by an even deadlier menace: the Bitmaps! Will they hold a clue to the origins of Candy, the girl who has become a flesh-and-blood video game character?
name: Roadside Distractions

description: Candy clings to life as her brother Matt tries to convince a doctor that his sister is really a living video game character. Can Matt get help before they're captured by the sinister Agent Korben? Plus, Matt's dad discovers some strange happenings at work that might provide clues to Candy's true origin!
name: Running on Empty

description: All the pieces of the puzzle start coming together, as the real motivations of Roland Childes, the owner of the video game company that created iCandy, are exposed! Plus, the true origins of Candy are revealed as she battles with the enigmatic Korben.
name: Childes' Play

description: Startling Series Finale! Trapped in the IFX headquarters building, Candy and Matt fight for their lives against the bitmaps and find an unlikely ally in Korben. But will Candy be forced to make the ultimate sacrifice to save her brother's life?
name: Interface

description: After a visit to an Egyptian exhibit at the museum, Lisa is inspired to create her own history project for a tomb featuring Malibu Stacy as Queen Cleptopetra with surprising results. Then, someone is defacing all the billboards around Springfield by drawing mustaches on them, but if El Barto isn't the culprit, who is? Finally, Bart gets a shot at redemption with the department store Santa.
name: A Tomb With A View; Tut-Tut, Tut!; Maggie's Crib; Bart vs. Bart; The Day of the Mustache; The More, The Merrier!

description: Mojo Jojo has had it with the Powerpuff Girls, so he's taking them to court! Can they handle the verdict? Plus, Grim has often thought Billy and Mandy would drive him crazy, but now he's actually in an asylum!

description: The Bean Scouts want to win the Bullfrog Races, but their contestant is too skinny! Plus, Ami and Yumi discover that not all free swag is good swag.
As the reigning Game Master of Foster's, Bloo promises to exhibit fairness and good sportsmanship... NOT! Plus, Camp Lazlo and the Eds!
Eduardo has lost his lucky penny. and he's going to search Foster's Home until he finds it, no matter what anyone else says! Plus, The Grim Adventures of Billy & Mandy and The Powerpuff Girls!
A new dance craze is shaking up Camp Kidney! But the prizes may be more trouble than they're worth. Plus, the Powerpuff Girls and Johnny Bravo.
